-- Jimmie Johnson Wins Record Fifth Straight Nascar Sprint Cup Championship
-- B y   E r i k   M a t u s z e w s k i
-- 2010-11-21T22:40:20Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-21/jimmie-johnson-wins-record-fifth-straight-nascar-sprint-cup-championship.html
Jimmie Johnson claimed his record
fifth straight Sprint Cup Series championship after a second-
place finish at Nascar’s season-ending race.  Johnson, 35, came in second to winner Carl Edwards at the
Ford 400 at Homestead-Miami Speedway and finished 39 points
ahead of Denny Hamlin in the season’s final standings. Hamlin,
who entered the season-finale with a 15-point lead over Johnson,
placed 14th in today’s race.  Kevin Harvick, who ran third today, finished 41 points
behind Johnson in the standings. Johnson won six races in 36
starts this season.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Erik Matuszewski at 
 matuszewski@bloomberg.net  